  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal Profile)",
  "description": "This model has been applied in clinical research settings to predict hemolysis in centrifugal blood pumps operating under ventricular assist device conditions. The CFD hemolysis model for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump was assessed under a Minimal credibility profile. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across operating envelope conditions representative of VAD implant populations. Thirteen credibility factors were evaluated; seven were formally assessed and six were flagged as epistemic gaps at Model Risk Level 5. The assessment team concluded that, within the scope of prior clinical research applications, the model achieves sufficient credibility for the intended comparative use. Decision: Accepted.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5-req-001",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-cfd-claim-001",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fda-centrifugal-pump-cfd-v2",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-experimental-hemolysis-dataset",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/vad-operating-conditions-montecarlo-inputs"
  ],
